  "text": "Mothers generally felt less confident at two months than at six months. This finding is consistent with other research showing that the earliest months as a parent can be stressful and challenging, especially concerning difficulties in soothing and comforting the infant [CITATION_1] , infant crying [CITATION_2] , and sleep disturbances [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
